                            <comment id="15256" author="rhenwood" created="Tue, 31 May 2011 08:58:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the advice.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;RHEL6 set: CONFIG_SECURITY_DMESG_RESTRICT=n&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m preparing a patch to copy this assertion for Lustre .config.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15255" author="brian" created="Tue, 31 May 2011 08:51:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In fact our policy with regard to kernel configuration options is to do what upstream does.  We want to change the config (when compared to upstream) as little as we need to to make Lustre work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So the right thing to do here is investigate what RH set this value to for RHEL6 and do the same thing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
